      "reasoning": "The mutation changes `blockIdx.x` to `blockIdx.y`, which fundamentally alters how threads are mapped to batch elements. In the original kernel, `dim3 blocks(batch_size)` creates a 1D grid where `blockIdx.x` ranges from 0 to batch_size-1. With `blockIdx.y`, all threads will have `batch_idx = 0` (since `blockIdx.y` is always 0 in a 1D grid), causing only the first batch element to be processed. All other batch elements will be skipped due to the early return check, but the output tensor is initialized to ones, so the final output will be all ones regardless of input. This creates observable differences when dropout is active during training, as the random number generation and dropout decisions will differ between processing only batch 0 vs all batches.",
